beer.beer_description:
A big Phat rounded American style stout, finished with a nitro charge.

To the eye
First up, thanks to a whack of Black and Roasted malts you will notice Phat Mongrel is as black as night, look more closely and you will notice fine beads of coffee coloured nitro bubbles rising from the black abyss to settle at the surface, forming a deliciously rich creamy head.

Up your nose
The pungent complex hop aroma will hit you between the eyes on first sniff.  Piny, resinous American hop notes fade way to reveal its rich roasty, chocolaty malt body.

In your mouth
Phat Mongrels assertive hop flavour and 70 IBUs of bitterness will have you gagging for more. The gentle alcohol warmth at 6.5% ABV and sweet Phat Chocolate and roast malt flavours will leave you well satisfied and content.

user.bio: I'm a craft beer enthusiast. I love hunting for hidden gems!  Cheers to my fellow beer lovers!!
I have been drinking good beer for many years but only recently got convinced to keep my tasting notes in Untappd.
Iniciando no mundo cervejeiro, com o fim de descobrir os sabores que a vida oferece...
I like playing fixing and teaching guitar and of course I like good beer :-)
Amateur beer taster looking to go pro.
